Food is necessary for humans because it provides the energy and nutrients needed for survival, growth, and overall health. The body requires carbohydrates, proteins, fats, vitamins, minerals, and water to function properly. These nutrients help in building and repairing tissues, strengthening the immune system, supporting brain function, and maintaining strong bones and muscles. Without proper food, the body becomes weak and more vulnerable to diseases. Food also plays an important role in mental well-being, as a balanced diet can improve concentration, mood, and productivity. Therefore, eating healthy and nutritious food is essential for living an active and healthy life.
